ABSTRACT



A lot can be done using simple accelerometer and gyroscope, these two are the sensors which we all carry in our pockets all the time. So any application based on them can be implemented easily as there is no need for the user to buy a new hardware device also a hardware device can be integrated with the existing technology in order to have some specific application. In our case we are making use GY-87(10DOF sensor) sensor with the processor Tensilica L106 32-bit with NodeMCU as microcontroller. Also we are focusing on visualization of the information on some desktop application.

We are recognizing the activity of the subject based on some features which are discussed in this report later, to calculate those features we are using just 6DOFs from our sensor that are x,y,z of gyrometer and accelerometer. Then those features are used to create dataset and that dataset is used to train the model. Later on our microcontroller will send the data to the server which can be local or can be hosted where a prediction will be made based on the trained model.



































1.
# 1.

# Introduction


1.1  Objective

We are recognizing the activity of the subject based on some features which are discussed in this report later, to calculate those features we are using just 6DOFs from our sensor that are x,y,z of gyrometer and accelerometer. Then those features are used to create dataset and that dataset is used to train the model. Later on our microcontroller will send the data to the server which can be local or can be hosted where a prediction will be made based on the trained model.

1.2 Key idea

Collecting raw data from the sensor and then extracting features from the collected data, the dataset will be made using these extracted features. Model will be trained using some suitable classification technique. Model will be stored in the local system, then a microcontroller enabled with wifi module will be used by the subject to send the extracted feature to the system using TCP/IP. We are planning to get the data using python socket programming and then python will pass the data to the pretrained model and then predict the result, predicted result will be sent to the database from where our software application can take the data and visualize it.



1.3 Expected challenges

1.  Collecting enough data so that a model can be trained to have some good accuracy. Also removing redundant data from the collected data.
2. Handling float data at microcontroller site that is required to be converted to char or byte in order to send it through TCP/IP.
3. Selecting less number of features in order to minimize the load on microcontroller and still get the significant amount of accuracy.

2.2 Choice of MCU

We are using NodeMCU because it is ultra low power 32bit device and also enabled with a wifi module, so if fulfills our requirement of connectivity and  high processing speed also it is low cost device so it is most suitable for the project. There is no alternative to it at  this price. So we finalized nodeMCU as our MCU for this project.

2.3 Circuit

As we are using gy-87 sensor which can be interfaced using I2C protocol and the protocol is directly and well supported by the nodeMCU. Circuit for the same is given below :

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

2.4 Getting raw values from the sensor

We are using I2Cdev library so we need not write I2C stack to get the data from the sensor and also we are using MPU6050 library decode the data.

accelgyro.getMotion6(&amp;ax, &amp;ay, &amp;az, &amp;gx, &amp;gy, &amp;gz);

mag.getHeading(&amp;mx, &amp;my, &amp;mz);

above are the commands to get the data from the raw data from the sensor and store them directly to the variables ax,ay,az,gx,gy,gz,mx,my and mz which are x,y,z values of accelerometer, gyroscope and magnetometer.

2.5 Extracting features

We are extracting 18 features mean,max,min for all three axis and for gyro and accelerometer.

we are taking a window or 100 sample, at a frequency of 50Hz which implies that 50 samples per second. So samples are taken and stored in the RAM in the form of an array then we are calculating all the features by adding, comparing and whatever functionality is required.

2.6 Storing calculated feature

Now data will be sent to a particular IP which will be obtained by connecting MCU to LAN of the PC where we listen for the data using python socket programming. But there is a challenge to be taken care of that is we need to convert the data to char or byte at nodeMCU side because we cannot send the data to a client in any other form and we need to decode the data at python side. To resolve the above problem first will concatenate all the feature obtained at MCU and then split the string into characters with some extra characters so we need not resolve the garbage value generated as we define the size of the character array so the extra characters will take care of variation in size due to sometime negative or positive value generated. code for encoding and decoding is given below.
